<HEADLINE>
PLUMMER QUESTIONS RE SULTS, NOT ABIL ITY TO MAKE PLAYS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By TIM TYERS  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, Ariz. - Cardinals quarterback  &UR; Jake Plummer was
drop-kicked by seven sacks in Seattle, threw two interceptions for
touchdowns and fumbled once, but he said Monday that nothing was
broken _ especially his confidence.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm frustrated by how I played,'' said Plummer, who completed
22 of 36 for 205 yards and a touchdown. ``I looked at the film and
I made some very bad plays. But I made good ones, too. If I keep
taking coach's advice and let the guys around me perform, I can
eliminate some of those bad plays.
</P>
<P>
   ``But my confidence is fine. If I had thrown six picks and we
got beat, I still have to come back and try to lead this team. Guys
are looking at me to be solid each week. I'm young, but I matured
enough last year to come out and say, `Hey, it's a new week, and I
can lead this team to victory.' '' &QL; 
Tobin takes over &QL; 
For the first time as Cardinals coach,  &UR; Vince Tobin became involved
in the offense when he sent in his ``tens package'' (two tight
ends, two backs and one receiver) for a series in the second period
with Arizona down, 17-0.
</P>
<P>
   A radio talk show took it to mean that his confidence in
offensive coordinator  &UR; Marc Trestman is cracking, but Tobin said he
was just trying to restore order.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't call any plays. We were having a hard time, and I was
trying to get something established,'' Tobin said. ``I think we
made seven yards but didn't get the three yards on third down.'' &QL; 
Sackless Simeon &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Right defensive end  &UR; Simeon Rice is sackless in nine games _ the
final seven of last season and the first two this season.
</P>
<P>
   ``His sack total is down from his rookie season (12.5), but when
a team has someone causing problems, they do something to stop
him,'' Tobin said. ``But he's doing much better against the run
than a year ago. He's an improved player all around. He'll get
sacks this year. I'm not concerned with that.'' &QL; 
Wadsworth report &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Tobin gave rookie defensive end  &UR; Andre Wadsworth, who made his
first start after only three practices, a so-so review.
</P>
<P>
   ``He did some good things, but also showed he hasn't been in
camp,'' Tobin said. ``He wasn't always in the right spot, which
hurt us on occasion, but he's going to be a very fine player.'' &QL; 
Injury report &QL; 
Tobin listed receiver  &UR; Rob Moore (hamstring) and center  &UR; Aaron
Graham (calf muscle) as questionable for Sunday, but Moore said he
expects to play, and Graham said he is day-to-day.
</P>
<P>
   Rookie offensive tackle  &UR; Anthony Clement, slowed by knee and
back injuries in the preseason, apparently re-injured his back and
his status is unknown. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
