<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-DOLPHINS16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Wooden out for season
 &HT;    By Mark Woods
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAVIE, Fla. _ Miami Dolphins safety Shawn Wooden joined
teammates Yatil Green and Larry Shannon: He underwent knee surgery
that will keep him sidelined for the rest of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Wooden, the Dolphins' starter at strong safety, had arthroscopic
surgery on his left knee to repair damage to the anterior cruciate
and medial collateral ligaments sustained Sunday on the opening
kickoff of the 13-7 victory against Buffalo.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's really disappointing,'' Dolphins coach Jimmy Johnson
said. ``Shawn had done a great job against Indianapolis (in the
season opener). He was really doing a good job as far as putting us
in the right coverages. We're disappointed that we're not going to
have him this year.''
</P>
<P>
   The loss means that if Calvin Jackson isn't hampered too much by
a groin strain, he will get the starting job that he battled Wooden
for during the pre-season. The Dolphins also will rely more heavily
on Brian Walker. They also could re-sign Bracey Walker, a four-year
veteran cut Aug. 19.
</P>
<P>
   The Dolphins plan to work out about six defensive backs today.
</P>
<P>
   ``We will take a look at making a few changes, but (the players
already on the team) are going to be the key players,'' Johnson
said. ``The biggest thing is that Calvin Jackson has got to get
healthy.''
</P>
<P>
   Marino and McGwire: The Dan Marino household includes a piece of
Mark McGwire memorabilia. In July, Marino gave his son, Joey, a bat
signed by McGwire for his ninth birthday.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't know what to get him, then I realized that he was a
big Mark McGwire fan,'' Marino said. ``So I tracked Mark down in
San Francisco and got him to sign a bat for Joey. Mark (shipped)
the bat to me and Joey was so excited. . . . Watching Joey get so
excited when he got that bat was a special thrill for me as well.''
</P>
<P>
   Marino and his family watched McGwire break Roger Maris' home
run record last Tuesday night. He had a good excuse for missing
Sammy Sosa catching McGwire at 62 on Sunday: He was playing against
the Bills at the time.
</P>
<P>
   Monday, the Dolphins released some comments from Marino, who
holds the NFL single-season record for touchdowns with 48 in 1984,
about McGwire.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think what I appreciate most is how he's handled the whole
thing, and the way he's conducted himself with all the attention
he's gotten,'' Marino said. ``The way he's so gracious dealing with
the press and the public just shows that he's a class act, and
people should appreciate that.''
</P>
<P>
   Disgruntled employee update: Receiver Charles Jordan says he is
over the frustration of losing his starting job to Oronde Gadsden,
but now tight end Troy Drayton is the one frustrated by a lack of
balls being thrown his way.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just have to play within the offense,'' said Drayton, who
has caught one pass for 9 yards in two games. ``What can you do?
Nothing. I can't do anything about it. I can do what they ask.''
</P>
<P>
   Jordan fumed most of last week. But Monday, although he still
was behind Gadsden on the depth chart, he said: ``That matter is
put behind us and we're looking toward going forward. Honestly,
it's all behind us.''
</P>
<P>
   Johnson greeted talk of unhappy players with a shrug.
</P>
<P>
   ``It would be great if everybody caught a lot of balls,
everybody had a lot of runs, and everybody had a lot of playing
time, but, hey, we're going to do whatever need to do to win
games,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   He also said that while Ed Perry has caught six passes for 35
yards, Drayton remains the Dolphins' No. 1 tight end.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you're only completing 14 passes a game and you've got
five or six guys, some guys are not going to get a lot of them,''
he said. ``The other thing is that Ed Perry has come on to be a
pretty good receiver for us. I don't know that I can guarantee
anything, but I think there are going to be games where Troy is
going to catch a lot of passes. But that's not our priority. Our
priority is to win games.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
