<P>
   SIBLEY-COLUMN _ Alabama Gov. George Wallace wasn't exactly a
stainless knight most of his life. He did some shocking and some
shabby things before, disabled and in pain, he took another hold on
life. But I read of his death with sadness. So much of life in the
South has been contending with demagogues and even as you deplored
their actions and attitudes you valued them for their colorful
ways. (Sibley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA: 7 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   SAVANNAH-CORONER _ SAVANNAH, Ga. _ Profile of Dr. Metz, the
Savannah coroner, who will be leaving on Saturday to go to Poland
to open a grave to get DNA material to compare with that from
remains found in Savannah, to see if said remains are those of
Casimir Pulaski, the Revolutionary War hero. Whew, despite all that
he's a pretty interesting character. Metz was mentioned in
``Midnight in the Garden of Good and Evil.'' He lives in a
converted funeral home on a square in Savannah, and he works as
coroner even though he's wealthy enough not to work at all.
(Hendrick, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS. ETA: 7 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   FASHION-DKNY _ Day 2 of the New York Fashion Scene. Designers:
