</P>
<P>
   SEAGRASS _ FORT PIERCE, Fla. _ A rare seagrass found in the Port
of Fort Pierce, Florida, has been added to the threatened species
list, a move that's likely to require extra care in dredging
operations. (Reeder, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ROOFIES _ Roofies, the Mickey Finn of the '90s, are now easier
to spy after they've been slipped into a drink. Drug manufacturer
Hoffmann-La Roche has reformulated the powerful sedative Rohypnol
so that it turns clear liquids blue and dark liquids cloudy,
thereby alerting unsuspecting people. Roofies is a street name for
Rohypnol, or flunitrazepam, which is legal in Europe and South
America, but not in the United States. (Kim, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA: 7 p.m.
</P>
