<P>
   FBN-BENGALS-ODONNELL _ CINCINNATI, Ohio _ Every time they step
on the field, the Bengals learn something new about quarterback
Neil O'Donnell. Of course, he commands attention in the huddle.
Sure, he can throw the deep ball. Yes, he's one tough customer.
``He's definitely a competitor,'' center Darrick Brilz said. ``A
lot of guys would have probably gone down. But he didn't. He kept
coming back. He fought. I know we can count on him.'' (Ludwig,
Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-DOLPHINS-ROOKIE _ DAVIE, Fla. _ Patrick Surtain and Sammy
Sosa have something in common. Neither player has the ball from the
most memorable play of his career. The Dolphins' rookie cornerback
was hoping to display the football that he caught for his first
interception, but Surtain was so excited about picking off a Rob
Johnson pass in the fourth quarter of Miami's 13-7 victory over
Buffalo Sunday, that he forgot to take the souvenir. (D'Angelo,
Palm Beach Post) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-DOLPHINS _ DAVIE, Fla. _ Miami Dolphins safety Shawn Wooden
joined teammates Yatil Green and Larry Shannon: He underwent knee
surgery that will keep him sidelined for the rest of the season.
(Woods, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
