Stever Spurrier is doing...and asking everybody else to do, too.
The Gators are 2-0, which isn't the problem. Well, kind of it is.
The victories have come against The Citadel and Northeast
Louisiana, which means they count only in a mathematical sense. The
Bulldogs and Indians, quite frankly, couldn't beat the Gators if
they ganged up and played 'em together. Also, it seems the Florida
offense _ having scored a mere 91 points _ is anemic. Which is why
it would be no surprise whatsoever to see Spurrier, come Saturday
night on the road in Neyland Stadium against sixth-ranked
Tennessee's nasties in the first Southeastern Conference game of
the season, fire up the engine on quarterback Doug Johnson and
throw him out there against the Volunteers. Because things get
serious now. Perhaps too serious, in Spurrier's opinion, for any
one quarterback. (Stoda, Palm Beach Post) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
