Manager Bryan Murray made a seemingly minor deal to acquire
goaltender Kirk McLean last March 20. ``At the time, I seriously
wondered if we would win another game,'' Murray said earlier this
summer. Three nights later, the slide ended at 13 games as McLean,
making his first start as a Panther, backstopped a 5-4 victory over
Montreal. McLean went on to go a respectable 4-2-1 in seven
appearances. So how did Murray reward him? He spent the whole
summer conducting a goalie search that ended with the free-agent
signing of Sean Burke last Saturday. Now McLean is hearing rumors
that he might be on the trading block yet again if Kevin Weekes
ends his holdout in time to make an impression in training camp.
``At this stage of the season, nothing is etched in stone,'' he
said. ``I'll be a free agent next year, and if they want to do
something, that's a business decision. All I can do is go out and
play hockey.'' (Biggane, Palm Beach Post) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
