too busy to tackle a novel. Short stories, perhaps? Too busy even
for that. Time enough to skim the newspaper and that's all. I have
a solution that will make happy readers of even the most
time-pressed folk, while also acquainting them with superior
literary fiction. Simple. They must read Saki. It isn't an Oriental
liquid or vehicle conveyance. It's an author, well nigh an
inimitable one. By LARRY SWINDELL. &QL; 
