<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Wednesday, Sept. 16 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact James Laurin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   CALIFORNIA-FOODMYTH (Los Angeles) _ A new study shows that
despite California's reputation as the land of health and beauty,
Californians eat fewer vegetables than other adults around the
nation and just aren't disciplined enough to get their five staples
a day. By Melissa Schmitt. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   GOOD-SAMARITAN (Los Angeles) _ In response to the murder of a
child at a Nevada casino, which was witnessed but not reported by a
friend of the murderer, the Los Angeles City Council voted to
expand its good Samaritan law to require anyone who sees a sexual
or violent crime against a minor to report it. By Patrick McGreevy.
(Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   REVERSE-HATECRIME (Palmdale, Calif.) _ An African-American man
was arrested in what deputies characterized as a hate crime for
yelling ``skinhead'' at a group of young white men and then hitting
one with his truck. By Bhavna Mistry. (Will move in the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
