<SLUG> BC-REVERSE-HATECRIME-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MAN ACCUSED OF USING TRUCK IN HATE CRIME
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BHAVNA MISTRY  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PALMDALE, Calif. -- A 21-year-old Palmdale man was in custody
after four young men said he called them skinheads, tried to run
them over and knocked one to the ground with his truck, sheriff's
officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Maceo Houge, an African-American, was arrested Tuesday on
suspicion of committing a hate crime and assault with a deadly
weapon -- the truck -- while the four white men, three of them 18
and one 19, walked across a shopping center parking lot Sunday,
sheriff's officials said.
</P>
<P>
   ``Maceo had tried to run over them,'' said Deputy Dave Miklos.
``The group said they did nothing to provoke the attack.''
</P>
<P>
   Justin Kender, 18, suffered bruises to one leg and was treated
at Antelope Valley Hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Miklos said the four friends told deputies that Houge cursed
them and called them skinheads after he drove into the parking lot
of the shopping center. Houge, accompanied by an African-American
female, allegedly drove toward the four, stopped short, drove
toward them again and hit Kender with his truck, Miklos said.
</P>
<P>
   Houge was being held at the sheriff's station in nearby
Lancaster in lieu of $60,000 bail.
</P>
<P>
   Palmdale is about 50 miles north of downtown Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   XXX
</P>
</TEXT>
