r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CAR-BOAT-TEX     09-15 0612
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CAR-BOAT-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HOPE FLOATS FOR BOAT IN RETURN TO TMS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 
By SIMON GONZALEZ 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Good things happen to Billy Boat when he
comes to Texas Motor Speedway.
</P>
<P>
   The Pep Boys Indy Racing League driver twice has raced at the
track in far north Fort Worth and twice has taken the checkered
flag.
</P>
<P>
   OK, his victory in the 1997 True Value 500K was taken away when
a postrace scoring audit revealed Arie Luyendyk was the real
winner. Boat still finished second, his career-best finish at the
time.
</P>
<P>
   And that was his second-best finish until he won the IRL night
race at TMS in June.
</P>
<P>
   ``We came back to Texas looking for a little vindication and
were able to get the victory for good,'' said Boat, who drives the
No. 11 Conseco Dallara/Aurora for A.J. Foyt Racing. ``I've always
enjoyed coming to the racetrack. I'm definitely looking forward to
coming back and getting back in Victory Lane.''
</P>
<P>
   Boat is looking for more good things as the IRL returns for the
running of the Lone Star 500K on Sunday, because nothing much has
gone right for him since he left TMS.
</P>
<P>
   After winning the True Value 500K, Boat's hopes came crashing
down when he wrecked at the next race, the New England 200. He
sustained a broken leg and fractured pelvis and missed the next two
races.
</P>
<P>
   He was second in the standings, three points out of first, after
winning at TMS. He has since fallen to 12th.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been a little bit frustrating since Texas,'' he said.
``We left there on such a high.''
</P>
<P>
   After his two-race absence, Boat returned to win the pole at
Pikes Peak International Raceway in Fountain, Colo., setting a
track record, and was running second late in the race. But his car
ran of gas two laps from the end, and Boat finished ninth.
</P>
<P>
   ``That was disappointing because we had a top-five, top-three
race car,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   He won the pole again and set another track record at the next
race at Atlanta Motor Speedway. It was his fourth pole of the
season, tying reigning IRL champion Tony Stewart for the series
lead.
</P>
<P>
   A mistake on a pit stop put him a lap down, but he got the lap
back and thought he could win the race. Instead, a wreck ended his
day.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had a really good race car at the end,'' he said. ``I felt
we could just drive through the field and go for the win. Then I
got tangled with a lapped car on a restart.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've been fast, we just haven't been able to put it all
together. It's frustrating when you feel you have a shot to win and
you have problems.''
</P>
<P>
   Boat has had enough problems. He returns to TMS trying to
salvage what once was a promising season.
</P>
<P>
   ``We'll try to win the pole and win the race,'' he said. ``We
haven't finished enough races this year. We need to come into the
last two races and get some good finishes, and try to get into the
top five in the points.''
</P>
<P>
   Boat said he is healthy enough to do it.
</P>
<P>
   ``As far as day-to-day, normal things you do I'm still
recovering,'' he said. ``But as far as driving the race car, I'm
100 percent. It's probably going to be another couple of months
before I'm back to where I can play basketball.''
</P>
<P>
   And he's definitely in the right place to do it.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you're a race driver, you always have places you go to
that seem to treat you better than other places,'' he said of the
1.5-mile trioval. ``Texas Motor Speedway has been one of those
tracks for me that I like to go to. It's a very fun race for the
whole team because it's in A.J.'s home state, we have a lot of
support there and I really love the racetrack.
</P>
<P>
   ``Any place you win on you like to come back to.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
