A6903 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BBN-BRAVES-ONDECK16-C     09-15 0276
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-BRAVES-ONDECK16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On deck: Philadelphia Phillies
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 1:10 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Turner Field.
</P>
<P>
   TV/radio: Fox Sports South, WSB 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: RHP John Smoltz (15-3, 3.10; 10-7,
3.74 lifetime vs. Phillies) vs. RHP Carlton Loewer (6-7, 6.06; 0-1,
63.00 lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Loewer came flying out of the Phillies system to win in
his first major-league start June 14, collect a 4-1 record in his
first six appearances and stroked the club's strong feelings for
his immediate future. Not so fast. Since July 17, Loewer, the
Phils' first pick in the 1994 out of Mississippi State, has won
just twice in 12 starts and is 1-4 since July. His run support has
been spotty. Six times in those 12 starts, the Phillies have scored
two runs or fewer. But Loewer also has been hit hard. He has
yielded 133 hits, including 16 homers, in his first 104 innings and
has walked 32 batters. He has faced Atlanta once, and it was his
worst night of the year; the Braves bashed him for seven hits and
eight runs in Philadelphia July 22, when he was lifted after facing
just 13 men. Andres Galarraga finished his night with a three-run
homer. Smoltz has not faced the Phillies this year. He is trying to
reach 16 wins for just the second time in his career, after winning
five of his last six starts and going 10-1 since the All-Star
break. He has allowed just six runs in his last 31 innings and his
9.2 strikeouts per nine innings is fourth-highest in the league.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
