<HEADLINE>
CLINTON, FELLOW DEMOCRATS EXPECTED AT FUND-RAISER TONIGHT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JILL ZUCKMAN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ President Clinton and Massachusetts Democrats will
gather Thursday night at the Park Plaza Hotel to raise money for
candidates running for the US House and Senate.
</P>
<P>
   Among those invited are three House Judiciary Committee members,
who are expected to sit in judgment of the president.
</P>
<P>
   Representative Barney Frank, a Massachusetts Democrat, said he
plans to attend unless major votes in the House get in the way.
Frank said he sees no conflict in appearing with the president,
since every member of the House will ultimately vote on his
punishment.
</P>
<P>
   Representative William D. Delahunt, a Massachusetts Democrat,
will not fly to Boston Thursday night, an aide said, because the
House will be in session.
</P>
<P>
   And Representative Martin T. Meehan said he would like to attend
the unity dinner if he is able to coordinate it with votes in the
House.
</P>
<P>
   ``During the course of my being a member of Congress, you have
interaction with the president, but that is not going to cloud my
judgment,'' Meehan said.
</P>
<P>
   Democratic Party officials are considering chartering a plane
from Washington for the event. Besides Clinton, Senate Democratic
leader Tom Daschle and House Democratic leader Richard A. Gephardt
are expected to attend.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
