<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 16
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CLINTON-CONGRESS-NYT (moved on Wednesday, September 9)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday,
September 9, about the report sent to the House of Representatives
by Kenneth W. Starr misstated the action taken by the House last
year against Speaker Newt Gingrich. He was reprimanded, not
censured, for ethics violations.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-WEB-MYSTERIES (moved on Wednesday, August 26)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, August
26, about Web sites for mystery fans referred incorrectly to Jiro
Kimura, who runs the Gumshoe site (www.nsknet.or.jp/jkimura). Jiro
Kimu-ra is a man, not a woman.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
