<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DROPPING IN TO SAY HELLO TO BILL
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Eleanor Mondale &LR; , glamorous CBS entertainment reporter, told
the Washington Post that  &UR; Monica Lewinsky &LR; 's suspicions about her
friendship with  &UR; Bill Clinton &LR;  are completely unfounded.
</P>
<P>
   The Starr report related how Lewinsky showed up at the Oval
Office one day last December, and  &UR; Betty Currie &LR;  told her she
couldn't see him because he ``already had a guest.'' Lewinsky said
she waited for 40 minutes, but after a Secret Service agent let
slip that the guest was Mondale, Lewinsky ``stormed away.''
</P>
<P>
   A report footnote says Lewinsky thought the two were
``romantically involved.'' Clinton was said to have been ``irate''
that Lewinsky had learned Mondale was visiting.
</P>
<P>
   Mondale, who has been pictured several times jogging with the
president, told the Washington Post that Lewinsky's ``speculation
is baseless, and has absolutely no foundation in fact.'' A
statement she issued through CBS said, ``I was in Washington, D.C.,
to cover the Kennedy Center Honors. I briefly stopped at the White
House to say hello on my way from the airport to interview the
honorees, as our families have been friendly for decades.''
</P>
<P>
   ( &UR; Carl Grunfeld &LR;  noticed that Saturday's San Francisco
Chronicle, packed with excerpts from the report, also included
 &UR; L.M. Boyd &LR; 's Grab Bag, in which &UR; Friedrich Nietzsche &LR;  opined: ``Two
things are wanted by a true man, danger and play. Therefore, he
seeks woman as the most dangerous toy.'')
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MADONNA OFFENDS SOMEONE ELSE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The World Vaishnava Association has issued a statement
protesting  &UR; Madonna &LR; 's wearing of a see-through blouse and Hindu
facial marking at last week's MTV Music Video Awards.
</P>
<P>
   ``Madonna's MTV stage performance, which combined Eastern
mysticism with Western hedonism, did not sit well with sincere
Hindus, Vaishnavas and yoga practitioners around the globe,'' said
the statement. Spokesman  &UR; Tusta Krishnadas &LR;  said that the singer
had ``offended Hindus and Vaishnavas throughout the world.''
</P>
<P>
   Madonna's response, issued through her publicist,  &UR; Liz &LR; 
 &UR; Rosenberg &LR; : ``The essence of purity and divinity is nonjudgment.
They should practice what they preach. If they're so pure, why are
they watching TV?'' And if that lacks a little in contriteness,
Madonna ``certainly had no intention of insulting anyone,'' said
Rosenberg.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MAKING IT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Married couples in dual-income households make love just as
often as couples where the woman stays home, say researchers at the
University of Wisconsin. The numbers, from a paper report in the
Journal of Family Psychology: 5.96 times a month with homemaker
wives; 5.63 times with working wives.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUEEN SAYS NO &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Something's rotten in Denmark, and that isn't the right
adjective, but then ``Hamlet'' isn't the right play, either. The
situation is more like ``Romeo and Juliet.''
</P>
<P>
   The Danish newspaper B.T. reports that  &UR; Queen Margrethe &LR;  had a
``serious meeting'' with  &UR; Crown Prince Frederik &LR; , and told him to
to cut off his romance with  &UR; Maria Montell &LR; , a local pop singer.
Meanwhile, Montell told the Ekstra Bladet that she is ``no longer
dating Frederik. We still see each each other but as friends. We
come from two different worlds, and we found out that it can be
difficult to combine that.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUEEN SAYS MAYBE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Queen Elizabeth II &LR;  has told  &UR; Prince Andrew  &LR; that she has no
objections to his plan to build a three-hole golf course on the
grounds of Buckingham Palace, says a report in the Mirror of
London.
</P>
<P>
   The Palace gardens take up 40 acres, and Andrew is said to have
talked over his scheme with the palace gardeners.
</P>
<P>
   Andrew, who will leave the navy in less than two years, is
hoping to go into some kind of golf business. A friend told the
Mirror that he regards any day in which he doesn't play golf as a
day wasted.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``The drape, color and fabric have lent him a rich, deep look, &LR; .
I went one size larger in suits to give him a difference, give him
a little more character.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Stylist Shelly Levine telling DNR how she dresses Dylan
McDermott of ``The Practice.'' This item is presented as a fashion
tip for men who want ``a little more character.'' Again, size
matters.
</P>
