<P>
   (NYT23) NEW YORK -- Sept. 15, 1998 -- NY-ELECT-4, 9-15 -- Betsy
McCaughey Ross, New York's lieutenant governor, with her daughter,
voting Tuesday at Public School 169 in Manhattan. Formerly a
Republican, she was defeated in the Democratic primary for
governor. (John Sotomayor/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) NEW YORK -- Sept. 15, 1998 -- NY-ELECT-3, 9-15 -- Peter
Vallone, New York City council speaker, after voting Tuesday at
Public School 122 in Astoria, Queens. He defeated three other
Democrats for the nomination to oppose Gov. George Pataki. (James
Estrin/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
