NY-BAREXAM-DISABILITY, 9-15 -- Marilyn Bartlett, who won a federal
ruling that entitled her to extra help on the New York State bar
exam after she claimed a reading disorder. Advocates for those with
disabilities hailed the ruling Monday by the 2nd Circuit U.S. Court
of Appeals as an important victory. (Vic DeLucia/New York Times
Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
