President Clinton returning to the White House - and the Lewinsky
crisis - on Tuesday. Clinton hired a raft of fresh advisers and
dispatched his top aides to placate congressional Democrats, as
members of the House Judiciary Committee bickered over whether to
release a videotape of his grand jury testimony about Monica
Lewinsky. (Paul Hosefros/New York Times Photo)
</P>
